Fortress, Mr Price Group, Naspers May Move in Early Johannesburg Trading

-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 
2011-08-25T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/fortress-mr-price-naspers-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close. The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index
declined 255.14, or 0.9 percent, to 29,349.45 by the 5 p.m.
close in Johannesburg.  Fortress Income Fund Ltd. (FFA)  : The South African
capital fund said Financial Director Nick Hanekom had resigned
from the board of directors with immediate effect. The stock
fell 1.4 percent to 11.81 rand.  Mr Price Group Ltd. (MPC)  : The clothing and furniture
retailer releases a trading update. Shares in the company
declined 1.9 percent to 70.20 rand.  Mustek Ltd. (MST)  : The computer-services company
publishes results for the year ended June 30, which are expected
to show an increase of 50 percent to 60 percent in earnings per
share, the company said in a trading statement on Aug. 19. The
stock ended unchanged at 5 rand.  Naspers Ltd. (NPN)  : Africaâ€™s largest media company holds
its annual general meeting. Shares in the group fell 2.5 percent
to 329.50 rand.  Sun International Ltd. (SUI SJ): The hotel and leisure
group holds its annual general meeting. The stock gained 0.1
percent to 87 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
